Hereford Cathedral MS. O. VIII. 1=(x).

Folio, vellum, 16in. by 11in. Dated by Canon W. W. Capes as Sec, XIV late, or Sec. XV early,—probably the latter; in wooden covers, and chained. Writing very clear, in two columns; not foliated. No headings or marginal comments. On the inside of the cover, a XV-century hand, probably the owner’s, has written: “liber M(agistri) Oweyin' lloid’,'‘ and on the back of the volume, under a horn label‚l is written “ Ex dono magistri Oweni Lloyd quondam Canonici huius eccle- sie.” These notes are probably the source of an entry in the manuscript, List of Benesactors to He'reford Cathedral Library, to be found in the library3 under the heading “ Ex dono doctoris Oweni Lloyde huius ecclesie canonici '‘ the names of 26 MSS. are given,
